If you want to handle the possibility of a `NumberFormatException`, you can wrap the call to `parseInt()` in a try-catch block like this:

```java
try {
    String str = "abc";
    int num = Integer.parseInt(str);
} catch (NumberFormatException e) {
    System.out.println("The string cannot be parsed as an integer.");
}
```

In this example, if the string "abc" cannot be parsed as an integer, a message will be printed to the console instead of causing the program to crash.

